The paper deals with coordination mechanisms and optimization of social cost in congestion games, which are topics that fall under game theory (cs.GT) and network economics (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of variable delays, which is a concept related to distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper proposes a mechanism that leads to a socially optimal outcome, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and social networks (cs.SI).
